de.ityx.ocr.ocrservice.vocr.characterdecision

Class VotingCharacterDecision

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.ityx.ocr.ocrservice.vocr.characterdecision.VotingCharacterDecision
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CharacterDecision

    @NotThreadSafe
public class VotingCharacterDecision
extends Object
implements CharacterDecision
    Implements the virtual OCR (VOCR) engine by applying the given VOCRModel. A VOCRModel instance must be trained beforehand by calling VOCRTrainer.trainWithErrorModel(java.util.List, String). The resulting model can be set by calling setModel(de.ityx.ocr.ocrservice.vocr.persistence.VOCRModel) and loadModel(String), respectively. A VOCR prediction can be retrieved with decide(de.ityx.ocr.ocrservice.vocr.dto.CharacterAlternatives). The prediction is wrapped in a CharacterGroup and consists of two parts:
    • the actual character String prediction
    • a confidence for that String prediction. The confidence value lies within the interval [0.0, 1.0] whereas a value of 1.0 indicates a high confidence.
